# QEMU Linumiz — TriCore Emulation Reference

## Confirmed capabilities

The QEMU Linumiz fork (`qemu-system-tricore`) correctly emulates a TriCore AURIX SoC:

- **STM0**: free-running counter and CMP0 compare-match interrupt work correctly.
  Ticked timer via `CMP0 += period` re-arm in the ISR is the canonical approach.
- **MPU**: data and code protection ranges enforced; access violations raise class 1 traps.
- **Atomic instructions**: `LDMST`, `SWAP.W`, `CMPSWAP.W` behave correctly.

## Machine

```
KIT_AURIX_TC397B_TRB   (TC3xx, QEMU -machine flag)
```

## Address map (TC397B)

| Region | Base | Size | Note |
|---|---|---|---|
| PFlash (NC) | 0x80000000 | 2 MB | code |
| CPU0 DSPR | 0x70000000 | 240 KB | kernel RAM |
| STM0 | 0xF0001000 | — | system timer |
| SRC IR base | 0xF0038000 | — | `TC39X_SRC_STM0_SR0 = offset 0xC0 → 0xF0038300` |
| QEMU virt console | 0xBF000000 | 4 KB | putchar / exit |

## Rules

- **No polling fallback**: timer interrupts are mandatory. `ULMK_ARCH_IDLE_IS_WAIT=0`
  (NOP idle) is required in all QEMU builds to keep the instruction counter advancing.
- **No TSIM**: TSIM has been removed. QEMU is the sole emulation environment.
- **No workarounds**: QEMU emulates TriCore correctly; no software emulation of
  hardware features is permitted.
